Gallbladder is mildly distended with a large nonmobile stone in the gallbladder neck, no gallbladder wall thickening, mural edema, or pericholecystic fluid. Positive ___ sign during the exam. The pancreas appears within normal limits; spleen normal echogenicity; kidneys without mass, stone, or hydronephrosis.
